#text=Today I decided to bake a cake so we could have it for dessert with tonight 's dinner .
#text=I thought a chocolate cake would be nice , so I took out my cookbook and looked for a recipe for chocolate cake .
#text=There were a few different chocolate cake recipes , but I picked one that was called devil 's food cake .
#text=The recipe had a list of ingredients , so I checked my cupboard to make sure I had everything I would need .
#text=When I was sure I did , I got out 2 mixing bowls and a cake pan .
#text=The recipe said to preheat the oven to 350 degrees , so I turned the oven on and set the temperature for 350 .
#text=Then I took a bit of butter and rubbed it all over the inside of the cake pan .
#text=That would make sure the cake did n't stick in the pan and I would be able to get it out without any trouble .
#text=I got out my electric mixer and put the beaters in , then plugged the mixer in the electrical outlet .
#text=As I read the directions from the recipe , I put the butter and sugar in one of the bowls .
#text=I put the beaters in the bowl and turned on the electric mixer , holding it really tightly as it mixed the butter and sugar until it was fluffy .
#text=I cracked some eggs , and added them to the bowl and beat that some more .
#text=In another bowl I mixed flour , baking powder , cocoa powder and all the rest of the dry ingredients .
#text=Then I mixed the wet ingredients with the dry ones and mixed them all together with the electric mixer until the batter was smooth .
#text=When it was , I poured the batter in my cake pan and put it in the oven .
#text=The recipe said it would take 30 minutes to cook , so I looked at the clock in my kitchen to see what time it was .
#text=Then I added 30 minutes to the time and knew when my cake would be ready .
#text=When 30 minutes was up , I opened the oven and looked at the cake .
#text=It looked done , but to be sure I took a toothpick and stuck it in the middle of the cake .
#text=If it came out clean , I 'd know the cake was done .
#text=If it came out full of wet cake batter , it was not done yet , and would need a bit longer to cook .
#text=I put on a potholder glove so I would n't get burned and removed the cake from the oven .
#text=I put it on a wire rack on my kitchen counter so it could cool off before I tried to take it from the pan .
#text=When it was cool , I flipped the pan over onto the rack and the cake fell out of the pan .
#text=It looked good , and I knew everyone would enjoy the chocolate cake that night at dinner .
